narratives.question_text: Please rate and comment on the following aspects of your experience in this course or module regarding: Workload
comments: Just enough work to get the concepts, but never a burden. Only the practical experience, no fluff. Exactly what was needed for this course.
You never know how much or how little Harry will give on any given week. This makes it tricky to plan schedules.

narratives.question_text: Please comment on all aspects of your experience in this course or module regarding: Organization.Comments:
comments: Simple meat-and-potatoes class - very little lectures, lots of discussion. Sequence was logical. There was no syllabus - wasn't confusing to me, but seems to have tripped up a couple classmates.

This class certainly had more organization than Harry's other course but it was far from organized. We often went on tangents or did not make it as far as you'd think we were capable of on any given day.

narratives.question_text: Please comment on all aspects of your experience in this course or module regarding: the Instructor.Comments:
comments: Only suggestion would be to ask Harry to pace his feedback in actual class sessions so that he could actually get to discussing everybody's assignment during class. Some classmates only got 1-2 sessions of personal feedback in the 7-week course, while others got 6-7. And if he doesn't do in-class feedback, it would be extremely helpful to have more robust written feedback.

Oh Harry...I love having Harry around but I do think this could be a workshop or two and not seven different sessions. He just isn't inclined to use the time in an effective way but he still has wisdom to impart.

narratives.question_text: Please comment on: Visitors, if any
Please comment on all aspects of your experience in this course or module regarding: Your Learning.Comments:
comments: Very glad to have taken this class, and to emerge with a pair of perfected templates with which to approach future negotiations. It's knowledge I wouldn't have had otherwise had, but crucial knowledge to have.
Again, I learned a lot about how contracts and separation agreements can work but I do not know that I will maintain it all.
Make this course a workshop rather than a full seven sessions.
